Inside Box has a Coordinate System, which is a mapping from the data's (x,y) to the SVG's (x,y) coordinats
Usually this is two 1D mappings, but for polar coordinates, map projections, or other systems, it's 2D map.
The scales are each 1D maps of some variable r cos(th) and r sin(th) for polar coordinates
* Axis line: defines zero of box (full or data-range)
* Ticks: (spcified, auto, or data-points) (length) (top or bottom of axis)
* Tick Label: (specified, auto, or data-points) (font) (top or bottom of axis)
* Axis Label: (specified or from some data) (top or bottom of axis)
